-- 1. [Problem Restatement] Show that (29¹³ − 5¹³) ≡ 3 (mod 7). 2. [Key Idea] Reduce each base modulo 7 and invoke Fermat’s Little Theorem (FLT: a⁶ ≡ 1 (mod 7) for a ≠ 0 mod 7). 3. [Proof] Method 1 (direct reduction + FLT) a) 29 ≡ 1 (mod 7) ⇒ 29¹³ ≡ 1¹³ = 1 (mod 7). b) 5 ≡ 5 (mod 7) and FLT gives 5⁶ ≡ 1 (mod 7). Since 13 = 2·6 + 1, write 5¹³ = (5⁶)²·5 ≡ 1²·5 = 5 (mod 7). c) Therefore 29¹³ − 5¹³ ≡ 1 − 5 ≡ −4 ≡ 3 (mod 7). Method 2 (cyclic pattern) Compute successive powers of 5 mod 7: 5¹ ≡ 5, 5² ≡ 4, 5³ ≡ 6, 5⁴ ≡ 2, 5⁵ ≡ 3, 5⁶ ≡ 1, then the cycle (length 6) repeats. 13 mod 6 = 1 ⇒ 5¹³ ≡ 5¹ ≡ 5 (mod 7). Combine with 29¹³ ≡ 1 to reach the same conclusion. 4. [Conclusion] Hence 29¹³ − 5¹³ ≡ 3 (mod 7).
